          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">8 for 110 swap</h2> 
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-jan-31-1.png" alt="8 for 110 swap" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>Summary: Another round of hostages and prisoners was exchanged on Thursday on the same day that UNWRA had to be out.</strong></p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Eight hostages were <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-31-01-2025-h1-1-handed-over?source=website" target="_blank">handed over</a> today to the Red Cross in exchange for 110 Palestinians. Three of them were Israeli, while five of them were Thai nationals. However, there was a pause in the Palestinian release due to his anger at the crowds surrounding Israeli captive Arbel Yehoud as she was released in Khan Younis (<a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-31-01-2025-h1-2-see-video?source=website" target="_blank">see video</a>).</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Hamas also acknowledged on Thursday that their military <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-31-01-2025-h1-3-commander-was-killed?source=website" target="_blank">commander was killed</a>. Al-Qassam Brigades did not disclose details on the circumstances of their deaths but said they "fell in battle against Israeli forces during the Al-Aqsa Flood operation." The war has killed more than 47,400 Palestinians and injured more than 111,000 since Oct. 7, 2023.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">In addition, <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-31-01-2025-h1-4-unrwa-had-to-vacate?source=website" target="_blank">UNRWA had to vacate</a> its operations in Israel on Thursday. Israeli law forces UNRWA's international staff to leave Israel and restricts their operations in East Jerusalem, but the agency continues its humanitarian work in Gaza and the West Bank. Human rights groups stressed that these "laws violate basic human rights and Israel's duties as an occupying power," warning of dire humanitarian consequences.</p>
        </mj-text>
