          <strong>🇸🇪 Iraqi Islamic critic was murdered in Sweden</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Salwan Momika, an Iraqi man who previously staged multiple Quran burnings in Sweden, was murdered near Stockholm. His actions sparked <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-31-01-2025-br1-10-international-outrage?source=website" target="_blank">international outrage</a> and led to massive protests and diplomatic tensions with Muslim-majority countries. Swedish police arrested five suspects and are currently investigating whether the killing was streamed online. Momika first came to Sweden in 2018 and was granted a residence permit in 2021.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Monika was facing charges of incitement to racial hatred, with a verdict scheduled for the day after his death. Swedish authorities stated that his actions had impacted national security but were not responsible for his protection; the responsibility was for the local police. His killing adds to growing concerns over tensions related to immigration, hate speech, and freedom of expression.</p>
        </mj-text>
